main event: A round, bright white object, size of a basketball, resembling a bright star was observed in the sky for 10-15 minutes.
interesting points: The object was thought to be a satellite at first.
The object had a definite outline/was sharply outlined.
The object appeared to stand still at times.
The object was observed from a location on Route 48 in Waynesville, Ohio.
The witness was unsure of the object's distance and speed.
sighted object: Round, bright white object, size of a basketball
